<Section title="Torsion">

<strong>Torsion</strong> refers to the twisting of a specimen when it is loaded by couples (or <strong>moments</strong>) that produce rotation about the longitudinal axis. Applications include aircraft engines, car transmissions, and bicycles, etc.

</Section>

<SubSection title="Units">

Force X distance [lb-in or N-m]

</SubSection>

