In general, the maximum shear stress is given by <DisplayEquation equation="\\phi = \\frac{TL}{GJ}\\" />

 For thin-walled shafts: <DisplayEquation equation="\\tau_{max} = \\frac{T}{2tA_m}\\" />

 where <DisplayEquation equation="\\begin{align} A_m &= \\pi R_{ave}^2 \\\\ R_{ave} &= \\frac{R_o + R_i}{2} \\end{align}" />

 Note that is NOT the cross sectional area of the hollow shaft!

